I would suggest trying a different spool of filament. I think that eliminating bad filament is easier than making changes to gcode/printer.
After that, it could be many things - as mentioned above retractions, speeds etc.

One other thing, I would look at is part cooling. Especially during the first layer, you can try to lower the speed of the part cooling fan, so there is more time for the extruded plastic to stick to the bed before cooling down. It didn’t seem to me as a big thing at first, but cooling can make a big difference in print quality.
